Villa fans had begun to call for an end to Paul Lambert’s reign when Christian Benteke sent a half-volley into the net a minute from time.

A year to the day since Sheffield United humbled Aston Villa in the third round, this match was on the verge of turning into another disaster.

Benteke’s strike silenced the protest at the end of a tepid encounter. 

