As in recent games, Benteke was looking a forlorn figure, but improved and forced Lewis to palm a fine drive onto the woodwork. 

Given was needed to tip a fierce shot from substitute Ishmael Miller over. With 60 seconds of normal time to play, Benteke struck.

‘I don’t think we deserved that,’ said Clark. ‘I can’t fault my team, I thought they were outstanding.’ 

